<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="82" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1086,1282]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,309,1086,1109]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new genus is very similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Fieber, 1866" authorityName="Fieber" authorityYear="1866" box="[708,962,1086,1109]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Phlepsius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[708,812,1086,1109]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">Phlepsius</emphasis>
Fieber, 
<number box="[909,962,1086,1109]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" value="1866.0">1866</number>
</taxonomicName>
with the connective (
<figureCitation box="[1211,1294,1086,1109]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1537,1559]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,191,1505]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,191,1515]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 12. Brevivalvala melanosticta sp. nov. 6. Male pygofer side, lateral view; 7. Valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; 8. Style, dorsal view; 9. Aedeagus, ventral view; 10. Aedeagus, lateral view; 11. Connective, dorsal view; 12. Profemur and protibial, anterior view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259706/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">
Fig. 
<number box="[1266,1294,1086,1109]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Zahniser" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" refString="Zahniser, J. N. &amp; Dietrich, C. H. (2013) A review of the tribes of Deltocephalinae (Hemiptera: Auchenorrhyncha: Cicadellidae). European Journal of Taxonomy, 45, 1 - 211." type="journal article" year="2013">
Zahniser &amp; Dietrich, 
<number box="[252,308,1120,1143]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" value="2013.0">2013</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, Fig. 
<number box="[368,396,1120,1143]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" value="46.0">46</number>
J) with stem short but can be easily distinguished from 
<emphasis box="[988,1081,1120,1143]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">Phlepsiu</emphasis>
s and other genera of the tribe by the aedeagal shaft with a pair of processes (
<figureCitation box="[614,679,1155,1178]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1537,1559]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,191,1505]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,191,1515]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 12. Brevivalvala melanosticta sp. nov. 6. Male pygofer side, lateral view; 7. Valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; 8. Style, dorsal view; 9. Aedeagus, ventral view; 10. Aedeagus, lateral view; 11. Connective, dorsal view; 12. Profemur and protibial, anterior view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259706/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">
Fig. 
<number box="[664,679,1155,1178]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
), the short valve (
<figureCitation box="[871,936,1155,1178]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1537,1559]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,191,1505]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,191,1515]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 12. Brevivalvala melanosticta sp. nov. 6. Male pygofer side, lateral view; 7. Valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; 8. Style, dorsal view; 9. Aedeagus, ventral view; 10. Aedeagus, lateral view; 11. Connective, dorsal view; 12. Profemur and protibial, anterior view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259706/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">
Fig. 
<number box="[921,936,1155,1178]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
), the subgenital plate without macrosetae (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1537,1559]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,191,1505]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,191,1515]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 12. Brevivalvala melanosticta sp. nov. 6. Male pygofer side, lateral view; 7. Valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; 8. Style, dorsal view; 9. Aedeagus, ventral view; 10. Aedeagus, lateral view; 11. Connective, dorsal view; 12. Profemur and protibial, anterior view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259706/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,165,1190,1213]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
) and with apices elongate, and style with short apophysis (
<figureCitation box="[793,858,1190,1213]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1537,1559]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,191,1505]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,191,1515]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 12. Brevivalvala melanosticta sp. nov. 6. Male pygofer side, lateral view; 7. Valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; 8. Style, dorsal view; 9. Aedeagus, ventral view; 10. Aedeagus, lateral view; 11. Connective, dorsal view; 12. Profemur and protibial, anterior view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259706/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">
Fig. 
<number box="[843,858,1190,1213]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
